text: For these experiments , we used two different strains of JEV , the Nakayama strain , originally isolated in 1935 ( 66 ) , and the more recent Laos strain ( 67 ) . Our results demonstrate a higher infectivity and level of replication for the Laos strain in both porcine NEC and macrophages . Associated with this was also a higher level of induced innate immune responses in epithelial cells . The reason for these strain - related differences is unknown , and strain and genotype effects require further investigations .
